\f0 \cf4 \cb3 \strokec4 Follow the brand.\'a0
\f1 \cb1 \

\f0 \cb3 The offer work should stay tight to Ribble\'92s design language, using the masonry layout as the foundation. Photography must be seasonal and grounded in winter gravel. Mixed surfaces, wet frames, quiet\'a0tracks\'a0and\'a0cold air\'a0belong here. Nothing forced. Nothing dramatic. Just real riding.\'a0
\f1 \cb1 \

\f0 \cb3 Bikes should be shown clearly and simply. Clean angles. Honest presentation. No styling that distracts from the product. The visuals should carry the feeling of February gravel.\'a0
\f1 \cb1 \

\f0 \cb3 Copy must stay short and direct. The offer should feel calm and factual. Save up to XX percent on gravel bikes is a piece of information, not a push.\'a0
